itemDescription: campaigner in the labour movement and Rector of the University of Edinburgh

wikipedia_page.main: Ann Henderson is a campaigner in the labour movement and former Rector of the University of Edinburgh.

link_mentions.page: Rector of the University of Edinburgh

response: Ann Henderson (1921–1976) was a Scottish sculptor.
Ann Henderson may also refer to:
*Ann Henderson (campaigner), Scottish labour campaigner and Rector of the University of Edinburgh
*Ann Henderson-Sellers (born 1952), Australian professor of environment and geography

In February 2021 when she was elected Rector of the University of Edinburgh, Kayembe became the third woman since 1858 to hold the role just after Muriel Gray and Ann Henderson. Her appointment was welcomed by her local MP Owen Thompson with a call for changes in the UK immigration laws.
